subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head-body 100 mm, tail 59 mm, hindfoot 19 mm (all measurements from the type specimen). No specific data are available for body weight. Condylo-incisive length is 23-6 mm. The Mount Malindang White-toothed Shrew is a large shrew, with a moderately long tail (59% of head-body length). It is larger than its congener the Mindanao White-toothed Shrew (C. beata), also of Mindanao. In size, it is comparable with other Philippine Shrews, such as the Mindoro White-toothed Shrew (
C. mindorus
), the Negros White-toothed Shrew (
C. negrina
), and the Palawan Whitetoothed Shrew(
C. palawanensis
). Compared to the Mindoro White-toothed Shrew, the tail is thicker with fewer bristle hairs and longer hindfeet; the cranium is more elongate, braincase slightly less globose, interorbital region broader, molars larger (10-1 mm). The Mount Malindang White-toothed Shrew is gray-brown with dark brown feet and tail, similar to the Mindoro White-toothed Shrew. It has a slight slaty tinge all over its pelage.
